9d04ce99-5656-4463-968d-ba2da6c755d7.079c2644-445d-483f-a541-bb707ca65e1f.prompt=User Identifier 9d04ce99-5656-4463-968d-ba2da6c755d7.110015d4-d121-4eaf-a75c-33bac56ff9a5.description=
Performs a mathematical operation on two numbers or strings

Inputs\:
value1 - The first value.
value2 - The second value.
operation - The operation to perform (+ - * ^ / > < \=\= \!\= >\= <\=).

Responses\:
success -  The operation completed successfully. If a boolean operation, it evaluated to true.
failure - Something went wrong or the boolean operation returned false.

Returns\:
The raw result of the operation, for boolean values this is true or false.

Returns\:
Field 1 - The first value. Here for compatibility
Field 2 - The second value. Here for compatibility
Field 3 - The operation. Here for compatibility
formatted_result - The formatted result of the operation, for boolean values this is true or false.
9d04ce99-5656-4463-968d-ba2da6c755d7.18ae960b-810a-47dc-b0fa-374454c89c96.prompt=Artifact ID 9d04ce99-5656-4463-968d-ba2da6c755d7.1d5c1e3d-31e4-495e-bc2b-72ba07398fd2.description=This workflow adds/ updates the component properties to Instance using Artifact APIs. onlyUpdate\: yes/no yes - To update values of existing properties no - To add and/or update properties keyValuePairs\: If you want to Add/update new properties\: property1 PUBLIC INTEGER 5 property2 PUBLIC STRING abc xyz If you want to only update the values of existing properties\: property1 5 property2 abc xyz 9d04ce99-5656-4463-968d-ba2da6c755d7.1ef03dcb-f55f-48fc-8917-e50b0db8ee3d.description=
Check the current date and time, and returns a java DateAndTime formatted string of it. If locale is specified, it will return the date and time string based on the locale.Otherwise, default locale will be used.

Inputs\:
localeLang - The locale language for date and time string. For example,  en or ja.
localeCountry - The locale country for date and time string. For example, US or JP. If localeLang is not specified, this input will be ingored.

Result\:
Current date and time.

Responses\:
success - Date/time retrieved successfully.
failure - Date/time could not be retrieved.
9d04ce99-5656-4463-968d-ba2da6c755d7.2ac03bc6-3cfc-4633-a270-c4073c082678.prompt=Component ID 9d04ce99-5656-4463-968d-ba2da6c755d7.3cb93bce-6214-41e9-98b7-72490ab1b578.prompt=User Identifier 9d04ce99-5656-4463-968d-ba2da6c755d7.42bbc285-ba8f-44c1-8506-b5763935672e.prompt=Component ID 9d04ce99-5656-4463-968d-ba2da6c755d7.48eb0673-9ade-4c85-b284-df3a4199cbdb.description=
Sends an smtp email
 
Input Parameters\:
hostname - hostname or ip address of smtp server
port - port smtp service is listening
from - from email address
to - email address(s) or recipients
subject - email subject
body - body of the email
htmlEmail - true or false, whether the email should be sent supporting html rich email.
readReceipt - true or false, whether or not to request a read receipt
attachments - comma separated list of files to attach (must be full path)
username - if SMTP authentication is needed, the username to send
password - the password to use
characterSet - the character set encoding for the entire email which includes subject, body, attached file name and the attached file. Default value is UTF-8
contentTransferEncoding - the content transfer encoding scheme (such as 7bit, 8bit, base64, quoted-printable etc) for the entire email which includes subject, body, attached file name and the attached file. Default value is - quoted-printable or Q Encoding.
 
 Responses\:
 success - successfully sent the email
 failure - failed to send the email

Note\:
For special characters (East Asian, right-to-left languages, etc.) you must install the support files on your local machine.
	For doing this on Windows go to Control Panel -> Regional and Language Options -> Language and check the options at Supplemental language support.
9d04ce99-5656-4463-968d-ba2da6c755d7.4ec2ed49-29ac-4c8e-b3a2-2d9c2b7164ff.prompt=User Identifier 9d04ce99-5656-4463-968d-ba2da6c755d7.53b3bfbd-51a6-4533-8591-760dcad7b29b.prompt=User Identifier 9d04ce99-5656-4463-968d-ba2da6c755d7.56fbad7a-356c-46fb-af43-738ca28b3d29.description=
Changes the time represented by a date by the specified number of seconds. If locale is specified, it will return the date and time string based on the locale. Otherwise, default locale will be used.

Inputs\:
date - The date and time to modify, formatted as provided by Get Current Date and Time.
offset - The number of seconds to change date by.
localeLang - The locale language for date and time string. For example,  en or ja.
localeCountry - The locale country for date and time string. For example, US or JP. If localeLang is not specified, this input will be ingored.

returns\:
A new date and time, formatted the same as the input.

Responses\:
success - The operation completed successfully.
failure - Something went wrong.
9d04ce99-5656-4463-968d-ba2da6c755d7.61db2886-7e72-4cd7-8046-bbd8957d043b.description=
The operation invokes web service methods.  This operation should not be used directly\!  Please use the wizard to build flows that use this operation.

Inputs\:
    xmlTemplate - The template of the soap request to make.
    inputMap - A map used to map between template names and user-friendly names. The template names are pipe-delimited xpaths of the xmltemplate location, with a numerical element for lists.
Value format\: A list of elements separated by the new line delimiter. Eache element hes the format\: \=.
Example\: A line in the "inputMap" could be\: "Request|Details|0|Input|x\=input0.x"
    url - The url to Post to. 
    header_SOAPAction - The SOAPAction http header field, defined by many web services for indicating the intent of the request
    wswAuthenticationType - The authentication type to use for the "username" and "password" input.
Default value\: http
Valid values\: http, ntlm, ws-security digest, ws-security text
    WSSecuritySignRequest - Should the SOAP request be signed using WS-Security.
Default value\: false
Valid values true, false
    WSSecurityEncryptRequest - Should the entire SOAP request be signed using WS-Security.
Default value\: false
Valid values true, false
    WSSecurityTimestampRequest - Should the Timestamp attribute be added to the WS-Security header
Default value\: false
Valid values true, false
    WSSecurityKeystore - Keystore to use for encrypting and signing requests.
    WSSecurityKeystoreType - The type of "WSSecurityKeystore".
    WSSecurityKeystorePassword - The password for "WSSecurityKeystore".
    contentType - Value to be used in the Content-Type HTTP header.
Default value\: text/xml
    characterSet - The character set for HTTP Get request and response.
Default value\: UTF-8
    username - The username to use for authenticating with the web service.
Value format\: For NTLM authentication, the required format is domain\user.
    password - The password to use for authenticating with the web service.
    trustAllRoots - Enables weak security over SSL. A SSH certificate is trusted even if no trusted CA issued it.
Default value\: false
Valid values\: true, false
    useCookies - Enables cookie tracking. Cookies will be stored between consecutive calls.
Default value\: false
Valid values\: true, false
    usesJSON - Use JSON arrays for the SOAP Request for all Array types.
Default value\: false
Valid values\: true, false
    timeout - a timeout after which the connection should be terminated or 0 for no timeout.
    socketTimeout - The time to wait for data to be retrieved, in milliseconds. This input needs a value greater than or equal to zero. A "socketTimeout" value of '0' represents an infinite timeout.
Default value\: 0
    proxy - A proxy to use when accessing the web service.
    proxyPort - A port on the proxy to connect to.
    proxyUsername - A username to use when connecting to the proxy.
    proxyPassword - A password to use when connecting to the proxy.
    keystore - The path to the keystore to use for SSL Client Certificates when using http authentication.
    keystorePassword - The password for the keystore when using http authentication.
    ICONCLUDE_WSW_VERSION - This value is used internally by the operation.
    returnXMLRequest - If this input is set to true, a new output named "rawXMLRequest" is returned from the operation which contains the text of the SOAP request that will be sent. This can be very valuable in troubleshooting.
Default value\: false
Valid values\: true, false

Results\:
    returnCode - This is the primary output. It contains the value 0 if the operation successfully completes and the value -1 otherwise.
    document - Raw XML response.
    documentStripped - Raw XML response stripped of namespaces for ease in parsing with XML XPath operations.
    jsonStripped - Raw XML response stripped of namespaces for ease in parsing with JSON operations, input usesJSON must be set to true for this to be populated.

Responses\:
    success - SOAP request completed successfully.
    failure - Something went wrong.

Notes\:
1.If wswAuthenticationType\=ws-security text then this operation transmits passwords in clear-text.
2.Any additional inputs that follow these are added by the Web Service Wizard, and they are specific to the particular web service method being called.
3.If you add new step-level inputs with the name header_, where  is the name of an html header, then that html header will be set to the given value in the HTTP request.
4.This operation will not allow connection through secure transport layers below TLS 1.0.

9d04ce99-5656-4463-968d-ba2da6c755d7.652ab49d-dd4e-4c76-92c9-6229b2f29831.prompt=User Identifier 9d04ce99-5656-4463-968d-ba2da6c755d7.65e65766-d045-412f-b5d5-347160e20f24.description=
Compares two strings, returning a true response if and only if they contain the same sequence of characters. A null string is considered to be equal to an empty string.

Inputs\:
    string1 - The first string. 
Default value\: "" (empty)
    string2 - The second string.
Default value\: "" (empty)
    ignoreCase - If set to 'true', then the comparison ignores case considerations. The two strings are considered equal ignoring case if they are of the same length and corresponding characters in the two strings are equal ignoring case. If set to any value other than 'true', then the strings must match exactly to be considered equal.

Responses\:
    true - If the two strings are equal.
    false - If the two strings are not equal.
9d04ce99-5656-4463-968d-ba2da6c755d7.6d54856a-a72e-4a8e-b568-96fedc29812c.description=
Check to see if the value stored in a specified flow variable, denoted by key, is null.

Inputs\:
keyName - The key to check, i.e. the name of the flow variable.

Returns\: 
The value in the specified key, i.e. flow variable.

Responses\:
isNull - If the key is a null pointer, i.e. the flow variable doesn't have an assigned value.
notNull - If some value is stored in the key, i.e the flow variable has a value assigned.
9d04ce99-5656-4463-968d-ba2da6c755d7.7631e736-ccaf-4909-94a2-48d218a0531a.description=This workflow adds/ updates the component properties to Instance using Artifact APIs. onlyUpdate\: yes/no yes - To update values of existing properties no - To add and/or update properties keyValuePairs\: If you want to Add/update new properties\: property1 PUBLIC INTEGER 5 property2 PUBLIC STRING abc xyz If you want to only update the values of existing properties\: property1 5 property2 abc xyz 9d04ce99-5656-4463-968d-ba2da6c755d7.78ddc857-120b-4443-930c-bdf918f7574f.description=
This workflow adds/updates the service component property using Artifact API.

Inputs-
componentId – Service Component  id
userIdentifier  - User Identifier id
displayName - Property Display Name to  add or update
propertyName – Property Name to add or update
onlyUpdate\: yes/no 
yes - To update values of existing property (In this case input "valueType" is not required , This input will not be considered even if provided)
no - To add/update property
valueType - Value type of the property. It can have value from selection list "HP CSA – Property ValueType". This Input is required only when Input "onlyUpdate" is selected as "no".
values - One or more values delimited by comma , (If user want to use some other separator for multiple values then needs to be pass as next input "separator")
separator - A delimiter that separates elements in the values ( default delimiter used is comma ,)
consumerVisible - Do you want to make property visible on consumer portal? (true/false), Default set to true
authType - The authentication type that this operation uses when trying to execute the request on the target server.
Valid values\: basic, form, digest, ntlm, kerberos, anonymous (no authentication).
Default value\: anonymous - authentication not used when executing the request.
kerberosConfFile - The path to the Kerberos configuration file. If this input is empty the kdc (Key Distribution Center) and realm will get their values from the full domain name which is obtained from the url of the web server.
timeout - The number of milliseconds to wait for a connection to be established. This input should be assigned a value greater than or equal to zero. A timeout value of zero is an infinite timeout.
Default value\: 0.
useCookies - If true, enables cookie tracking. Cookies will be stored between consecutive calls. This is a boolean input. If a non-boolean value is specified, it will take the default value.
Default value\: true.
proxy - A proxy to use when accessing the web site.
proxyPort - The port on the proxy to connect to.
proxyUsername - The username to use when connecting to the proxy.
proxyPassword - The password to use when connecting to the proxy.
encodeURL - If true, automatically encodes the URL. This is a boolean input. If a non-boolean value is specified, it will take the default value.
Default value\: false.
userAgent - The value that should be used if the HTTP header USER_AGENT has to be overridden.
trustAllRoots - If true, enables weak security over SSL. A SSL certificate is trusted even if no trusted CA issued it.
Default value\: true
keystore - URL of the keystore file or local path to it (e.g. %JAVA_HOME%/jre/lib/security/cacerts). It may be empty if HTTPS client authentication is not to be used.
keystorePassword - Password to unlock the keystore.
trustKeystore - URL of the truststore file or local path to it (e.g. %JAVA_HOME%/jre/lib/security/cacerts). It may be empty if HTTPS server authentication is not to be used.
trustPassword - Password to unlock the truststore.

Outputs-
document  – returned XML document from API

Stop a VPC server, 

The creds must be passed in the xml request, so they are extracted from the resource provider
Calls the VPC  server webservice, and passes the action string stop
and sets subscription  power state


Inputs Parameters\:

 CSA_CONTEXT_ID – CSA Context Id
 CSA_PROCESS_ID – CSA Process Instance Id
 SVC_COMPONENT_ID - This token will resolve to the Service component Id. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\:SVC_COMPONENT_ID]
 RSC_PROVIDER_ID - This token will resolve to the Resource Provider Id that was selected at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\:RSC_PROVIDER_ID]
 SVC_SUBSCRIPTION_EMAIL - This token will resolve to the subscriber’s email address. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: SVC_SUBSCRIPTION_EMAIL]
 RSC_SUBSCRIPTION_ID - This token will resolve to the Resource Subscription Id that was created from the Resource Offering at the Subscription time.
  		Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: RSC_SUBSCRIPTION_ID]
 SVC_COMPONENT_TYPE - This token will resolve to the Service component type. Eg\: Server.. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: SVC_COMPONENT_TYPE]
 RSC_POOL_ID - This token will resolve to the Resource pool Id that was selected at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: RSC_POOL_ID]
 SVC_INSTANCE_ID - This token will resolve to the Service Instance Id. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: SVC_INSTANCE_ID]
 SVC_SUBSCRIPTION_ID - This token will resolve to the Subscription Id that was created at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: SVC_SUBSCRIPTION_ID]
 PRN_COMPONENT_ID – This token will resolve to the parent Component’s Service Component Id. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: PRN_COMPONENT_ID]
 REQ_ORG_ID - This token will resolve to the Organization Id associated with the service request. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: REQ_ORG_ID]
 REQ_USER_ID - This token will resolve to the User Id associated with the service request. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: REQ_USER_ID]
 USR_ORG_ID - This token will resolve to the Organization Id associated with the subscriber. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: USR_ORG_ID]
 RSC_BINDING_ID - This token will resolve to the Resource Binding Id that was created at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: RSC_BINDING_ID]

Responses\:
 success - The operation completed successfully.
 failure - Something went wrong.

Schedule Flow - Schedules a flow or updates an existing schedule of a flow.

Inputs\:
    host - The target host for your request. The host can also be given as a URL.
    username - The username to use when connecting to the Central service.
    password - The password to use when connecting to the Central service.
    port - The port the Central service is running on.
Default value\: 8080.
    protocol - The protocol used to communicate to the Central service.
Default value\: http
Valid values\: http, https.
    trustAllRoots - If true, enables weak security over SSL. A SSL certificate is trusted even if no trusted CA issued it.
Default value\: false.
Valid values\: true, false.
    trustKeystore - The path of the truststore file. It may be empty if HTTPS server authentication is not to be used.
    trustPassword - Password to unlock the truststore. Provide this input only if trustKeystore is not empty.
    flow - The UUID or the path of the flow to run.
Example\: /Library/Integrations/Amazon/S3/Buckets/Enumerate Buckets
    schedule - The id of the schedule to update.
    names - A delimiter separated list of names of flow inputs.
    values - A delimiter separated list of values of flow inputs.
    delimiter - The delimiter separating lists of names and values.
Default value\: , (comma).
    description - A description of this schedule. If this input is set then the provided value will be the "Schedule Name" in Central/Run Management/Scheduler and after the execution of the scheduled flow will appear as "Run Name" in Central/Run Management/Run Explorer. 
Example\: "Scheduled Flow Created By ..."
    enabled - Set false to create the schedule disabled. This input is case insensitive.
Valid values\: true, false.
Default value\: true.
    startTime - The time to start running the flow either as minutes from now or as a date. Use the utility operations from "Date and Time" folder to pass valid startTime value.
Example\: Wed, 12 Dec 2012 12\:12\:12 GMT
Example\: Wed, 12 Dec 2012 12\:12\:12 GMT+0430 (4 hours, 30 minutes west of the Greenwich meridian).
    endTime - The time to end running the flow either as minutes from now or as a date. Use the utility operations from "Date and Time" folder to pass valid endTime value.
Example\: Wed, 12 Dec 2012 12\:12\:12 GMT
Example\: Wed, 12 Dec 2012 12\:12\:12 GMT+0430 (4 hours, 30 minutes west of the Greenwich meridian).
    timesToRun - The number of times to re-run the flow schedule. If empty, the number of times to re-run the schedule will be computed as (endTime - startTime)/repeatInterval. If -1 the flow will be scheduled to run indefinitely, otherwise this input must have a positive value.
    repeatInterval - Sets the time interval in minutes between schedule triggering. If empty, the operation will set it to 1 minute.

Returns\:
    returnResult - Thi is the primary output. The id of the schedule.
    flowUuid - The UUID of the flow. This can be useful if the flow input is the path of the flow.

Responses\:
    success - The schedule was created or updated.
    failure - Could not connect to central web service. Invalid inputs. Invalid flow path. The schedule ends before it starts. The schedule ends in the past.

Notes\:
1. "timesToRun" and "endTime" inputs are mutually exclusive.
9d04ce99-5656-4463-968d-ba2da6c755d7.d4043d68-3c41-43cf-b75f-dfbf663328c2.prompt=User Identifier 9d04ce99-5656-4463-968d-ba2da6c755d7.d5a7816d-30e4-4233-8ed8-fab0f6b8eb47.description=
Service to perform an HTTP GET via the Java HTTP Client

Inputs\:
url - the url to attempt to retrieve.
username - the username to authenticate to url with.
password - the password for username.
timeout - a timeout after which the connection should be terminated, or 0 for no timeout.
useCookies - Enables cookie tracking. Cookies will be stored between consecutive calls. valid options are\: true/false
followRedirects - specifies whether or not the get command should automatically follow redirects.
trustAllRoots - enables weak security over SSL. A SSH certificate is trusted even if no trusted CA issued it. valid options are\: true/false
proxy - a proxy to use when accessing the web site.
proxyPort - a port on the proxy to connect to.
proxyUsername - a username to use when connecting to the proxy.
proxyPassword - a password to use when connecting to the proxy.
encodeURL - perform URL encoding.
userAgent - if the HTTP header USER_AGENT needs to be overridden, pass in the value here
characterSet - the characterSet for HTTP Get request and response. Default is UTF-8.

Responses\:
success - URL retrieved successfully.
failure - The url could not be retrieved.
